    <h1 class="wikiTitle">WeblogMulticaster</h1>
<div id="wikiContent">
<a name="PageTop"></a>
    <div class="wikiMeta">Revision r1.5 - 08 Oct 2002 - 17:42 GMT - <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/TWikiGuest">TWikiGuest</a> <!--META{"parent" prefix=">br /<Parents: "}%--></div>
<p />
<h2><a name="Abstract"> Abstract </a></h2>
<p />
<p />
<h2><a name="Assumptions"> Assumptions </a></h2>
<p />
<ul>
<li> Many <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/WebLog">WebLogs</a> now support the <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">BloggerApi</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/BloggerApi?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a> via <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/XmlRpc">XmlRpc</a>, even <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/LiveJournal">LiveJournal</a> has a <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">BloggerToLj</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/BloggerToLj?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a> app written for it.
</li>
<li> Hosting one's content on multiple weblog services is a <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">GoodThing</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/GoodThing?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a>
</li>
<li> Different <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/WebLog">WebLog</a> services may be more appropriate for different content from the same person.
</li>
<li> Implementing <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">BloggerApi</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/BloggerApi?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a> allows one to take advantage of many authoring tools, current and future
</li>
<li> <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">DesktopWepAppServer</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/DesktopWepAppServer?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a> drop-in or server-based <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">WebService</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/WebService?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a>?
<ul>
<li> Either one should be multi-user
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p />
<h2><a name="Goals"> Goals </a></h2>
<p />
<ul>
<li> Could this be done with some modifications to <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/RadioUserLand">RadioUserLand</a>'s <a href="http://radio.userland.com/manilaBloggerBridgeTool" target="_top">Manila-Blogger Bridge Tool</a>?
</li>
<li> Handle categories
</li>
<li> Extensible
</li>
<li> Multiple <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/WebLog">WebLogs</a>
<ul>
<li> Reflect to other <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">BloggerApi</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/BloggerApi?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a> systems
</li>
<li> Relay the posting on to other <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/WebLog">WebLog</a> api's (ie. <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">LiveJournalApi</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/LiveJournalApi?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a>)
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Filtering
<ul>
<li> Select services at which to reflect based on category
</li>
<li> <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/WikiWiki">WikiWiki</a>-fy content as it passes through to be published
</li>
<li> Perform tasks based on a form of metadata (ie. "!"-prefixed head-of-document commands"
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p />
<h2><a name="Tasks"> Tasks </a></h2>
<p />
<h2><a name="Notes_URLs"> </a> Notes &amp; URLs </h2>
<p />
<ul>
<li> <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">RadioUserland</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/RadioUserland?topicparent=Main.WeblogMulticaster">?</a> - <a href="http://radio.userland.com" target="_top">http://radio.userland.com</a>
</li>
<li> <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/BloggerAPI">BloggerAPI</a>
<ul>
<li> <a href="http://plant.blogger.com/api/" target="_top">http://plant.blogger.com/api/</a>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Manilla-RPC
<ul>
<li> <a href="http://archipelago.phrasewise.com/stories/storyReader$883" target="_top">http://archipelago.phrasewise.com/stories/storyReader$883</a>
</li>
<li> <a href="http://www.xmlrpc.com/stories/storyReader$700" target="_top">http://www.xmlrpc.com/stories/storyReader$700</a>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Steve Hooker's category-enabled Manila-Blogger API tool
<ul>
<li> <a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/radio-dev/message/5149" target="_top">http://groups.yahoo.com/group/radio-dev/message/5149</a>
</li>
<li> <em>This sounds perfect, but it crashes my Radio :( -- <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/LesOrchard">LesOrchard</a> - 07 Mar 2002</em>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> wasabii API - web application standard API (for) bi-directional information interchange
<ul>
<li> <a href="http://wasabii.org/spec/body.php" target="_top">http://wasabii.org/spec/body.php</a>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
